{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Phase 4: Ablation Study & Evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, we compare the performance of Naive Bayes, Logistic Regression, and LSTM models using the predictions we saved in Phase 3. We will calculate Accuracy, Precision, Recall, and F1-Score, and visualize the results using Confusion Matrices and ROC curves."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "sys.path.append(os.path.abspath('..'))\n",
    "from src.evaluation import ModelEvaluator\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ensure results directory exists\n",
    "os.makedirs('../results/plots', exist_ok=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Load True Labels and Predictions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "try:\n",
    "    y_test = np.load('../data/y_test.npy')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    y_pred_nb = np.load('../data/y_pred_nb.npy')\n",
    "    y_pred_lr = np.load('../data/y_pred_lr.npy')\n",
    "    y_pred_lstm = np.load('../data/y_pred_lstm.npy')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    y_prob_nb = np.load('../data/y_prob_nb.npy')\n",
    "    y_prob_lr = np.load('../data/y_prob_lr.npy')\n",
    "    y_prob_lstm = np.load('../data/y_prob_lstm.npy')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(\"Predictions loaded successfully.\")\n",
    "except FileNotFoundError:\n",
    "    print(\"Error: Prediction files not found. Please run the Model Training notebook first.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Calculate Metrics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "evaluator = ModelEvaluator(output_dir='../results/plots')\n",
    "\n",
    "metrics_nb = evaluator.calculate_metrics(y_test, y_pred_nb)\n",
    "metrics_lr = evaluator.calculate_metrics(y_test, y_pred_lr)\n",
    "metrics_lstm = evaluator.calculate_metrics(y_test, y_pred_lstm)\n",
    "\n",
    "all_metrics = {\n",
    "    'Naive Bayes': metrics_nb,\n",
    "    'Logistic Regression': metrics_lr,\n",
    "    'LSTM': metrics_lstm\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "comparison_df = evaluator.generate_comparison_table(all_metrics)\n",
    "display(comparison_df.round(4))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save comparison table to results\n",
    "comparison_df.to_csv('../results/model_comparison.csv')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Visualize Metrics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "comparison_df.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(12, 6), colormap='viridis')\n",
    "plt.title('Model Performance Comparison')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Score')\n",
    "plt.ylim(0, 1.1)\n",
    "plt.legend(loc='lower right')\n",
    "plt.xticks(rotation=0)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('../results/plots/metrics_comparison.png')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Confusion Matrices\n",
    "Let's see where the models are making mistakes (False Positives vs False Negatives)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "evaluator.plot_confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_nb, 'Naive Bayes')\n",
    "evaluator.plot_confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_lr, 'Logistic Regression')\n",
    "evaluator.plot_confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_lstm, 'LSTM')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Confusion matrices saved to results/plots/ directory.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. ROC Curves and AUC\n",
    "We plot the ROC curves for all three models together to visualize their capability of distinguishing between positive and negative classes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model_probs = {\n",
    "    'Naive Bayes': y_prob_nb,\n",
    "    'Logistic Regression': y_prob_lr,\n",
    "    'LSTM': y_prob_lstm\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "evaluator.plot_roc_curves(y_test, model_probs)\n",
    "print(\"ROC comparison saved to results/plots/roc_comparison.png\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Conclusions\n",
    "Based on the ablation study:\n",
    "- The traditional ML models (Naive Bayes and Logistic Regression) provide a strong, fast baseline using TF-IDF.\n",
    "- LSTM, by capturing sequential dependencies and utilizing embedding vectors, should provide an improvement in the F1-Score, demonstrating why Deep Learning is the State-of-the-Art for NLP tasks.\n",
    "\n",
    "The results generated here can now be compiled into the final Research Report."
   ]
  }
 ],
